there was a little girl who lived in a village near the forest.  Most days she went to play in the woods and returned home in the evening.  She had a special fondness for red clothes, so she always wore a red riding cloak, although she rarely rode any horses.  One day she met a prince and asked her parents' permission to marry him.  Her mother agreed but her father refused and said he would only accept the marriage if the girl promised to wear red clothes
